    <h3>Technology</h3>
    <div class="card px-3 pt-3">
        <p><a href="https://phds.io">PhDs.io</a> is built with <a href="https://github.com/whiskyechobravo/kerkoapp">KerkoApp</a>, a web application that uses <a href="https://github.com/whiskyechobravo/kerko">Kerko</a> to provide a user-friendly search and browsing interface for sharing a bibliography managed with the <a href="https://www.zotero.org/">Zotero</a> reference manager.</p>

        <p>KerkoApp is built in <a href="https://www.python.org/">Python</a> with the <a href="https://pypi.org/project/Flask/">Flask</a> framework. It is just a thin container around Kerko and, as such, inherits most of its features directly from Kerko. However, it adds support for <a href="https://toml.io/">TOML</a> configuration files, allowing a good separation of configuration from code.</p>

        <p>To ensure fair use of the platform, <strong>we impose rate limits and temporary IP blocking for users who exceed reasonable access patterns</strong>. These measures are in place to prevent misuse and maintain the quality of service for all users.</p>
    </div>

